data.name: TableLayoutCorruptedLine1
data.value: The layout table is not valid at: row {0}, column {1}.
data.comment: First line of error message. If for some reason the code that manages the table structure in the view and form designer finds we have created an invalid table layout the error will show. The error will show when the table layout is recalculated. Some examples are: adding/removing a column/ row, merging a column/ row, selecting a table cell. {0} and {1} will contain a non zero indexed row / column number respectively.

data.name: TableLayoutCorruptedLine2
data.value: If you have not saved the view, discard your changes and try again. If you have saved the view, undo your checkout. Otherwise contact Nintex Support.
data.comment: Second line of error message. If for some reason the code that manages the table structure in the view and form designer finds we have created an invalid table layout the error will show. The error will show when the table layout is recalculated. Some examples are: adding/removing a column/ row, merging a column/ row, selecting a table cell

data.value: There was a problem loading site settings. If the issue persists, contact Nintex Support. {0} Click OK to retry.
